## 1) Diversity and Classification (Living World, Plant/Animal Kingdom)

### Taxonomic hierarchy
- Order: Species → Genus → Family → Order → Class → Phylum → Kingdom.
- Trick: “King Phillip Came Over For Good Soup” (Kingdom, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, Species).

### Five kingdoms
- Monera, Protista, Fungi, Plantae, Animalia.
- Trick: “My Father Put Green Pants On” (Monera, Fungi, Protista, Plantae, Animalia). 【turn1fetch1】

### Plant kingdom evolutionary sequence (cryptogams → phanerogams → classes)
- Thallophyta → Bryophyta → Pteridophyta → Gymnosperms → Angiosperms → Monocots → Dicots.
- Trick: “The British People Fight Against Marching Troops” (Thallophyta, Bryophyta, Pteridophyta, Gymnosperms, Angiosperms, Monocots, Dicots). 【turn1fetch0】

### Algae groups (with examples)
- Chlorophyceae (green): Spirogyra, Volvox, Chlamydomonas.
- Phaeophyceae (brown): Laminaria, Sargassum, Fucus.
- Rhodophyceae (red): Polysiphonia, Gelidium, Gracilaria.
- Trick: “Chlorophyll friends are green; Phaeo lovers are brown; Red roses are red (Rhodo).”

### Bryophyta characteristics
- Body: thallus (no true roots/stems/leaves).
- Rhizoids for fixation (not true roots).
- Dominant gametophyte; sporophyte dependent.
- Homosporous.
- Water essential for fertilization (motel number: amphibians of plant kingdom).
- Examples: Marchantia, Funaria, Sphagnum.

### Pteridophyta vs Gymnosperms vs Angiosperms
- Pteridophytes: vascular cryptogams; independent sporophyte & gametophyte; homosporous (some heterosporous e.g., Selaginella, Salvinia).
- Gymnosperms: naked seeds; no fruits; vascular tissues; heterosporous; prothallus (gametophyte) reduced; examples: Pinus, Cycas, Ginkgo.
- Angiosperms: seeds inside fruits; double fertilization; vessels in xylem (usually); examples: Mango, Wheat.

### Animal phyla (non-chordates) sequence and key traits
- Porifera → Cnidaria → Platyhelminthes → Nematoda → Annelida → Arthropoda → Mollusca → Echinodermata → Hemichordata → Chordata.
- Trick: “Porcupines Can Play Nicely And Move Everywhere Around Chicks” (Porifera, Cnidaria/Coelenterata, Platyhelminthes, Nematoda, Annelida, Mollusca, Echinodermata, Arthropoda, Chordata). 【turn1fetch0】
- Porifera: canal system; ostia, osculum; spicules.
- Cnidaria: cnidocytes; polyp and medusa; Cnidaria = Coelenterata.
- Platyhelminthes: triploblastic, acoelomate; flame cells (excretion); parasitic.
- Nematoda: pseudocoelomate; complete digestive tract; sexual dimorphism.
- Annelida: true coelom; metameric segmentation; nephridia.
- Arthropoda: chitinous exoskeleton; jointed appendages; open circulatory system.
- Mollusca: mantle; radula; muscular foot; visceral mass.
- Echinodermata: water vascular system; tube feet; pentaradial symmetry adults; larvae bilaterally symmetrical.

### Vertebrate classes (evolution order)
- Fishes → Amphibians → Reptiles → Birds → Mammals.
- Trick: FARBM (Fishes, Amphibians, Reptiles, Birds, Mammals). 【turn1fetch0】

