## 2) Cell: The Unit of Life; Biomolecules; Cell Cycle

### Cell theory (key points)
- Schleiden & Schwann: all plants/animals composed of cells.
- Virchow: “Omnis cellula e cellula” (all cells arise from pre-existing cells).
- Prokaryote: no membrane-bound organelles; nucleoid; 70S ribosomes.
- Eukaryote: true nucleus; 80S ribosomes (70S in organelles like mitochondria/chloroplast).

### Fluid mosaic model of plasma membrane
- Phospholipid bilayer + proteins (integral and peripheral) + cholesterol (animal cells) + carbohydrates (glycolipids/glycoproteins).
- Trick: Think “iceberg on a sea of lipids” (proteins float in lipid bilayer).

### Mitochondria & chloroplast (semi-autonomous)
- Own DNA & 70S ribosomes; double membrane.
- Mitochondria: cristae (site: ETS & oxidative phosphorylation); matrix (Krebs cycle).
- Chloroplast: thylakoids (grana) for light reactions; stroma for Calvin cycle.

### Biomolecules – enzymes
- Proteinaceous; tertiary/quaternary structure.
- Prosthetic groups: tightly bound cofactors (e.g., heme in catalase).
- Coenzymes: organic cofactors (e.g., NAD+, FAD).
- Inhibitors: competitive (binds active site); non-competitive (binds elsewhere); allosteric.
- Lock-and-key (induced fit) model.

### Cell cycle phases
- G1 → S → G2 → M.
- Interphase = G1 + S + G2 (longest phase).
- Trick: “GPS My way” (G1, Prophase, S, Metaphase) – actually easier: “IPMAT” for mitosis stages: Interphase, Prophase, Metaphase, Anaphase, Telophase.

### Mitosis vs Meiosis
- Mitosis: 2 diploid daughter cells; no crossing over; somatic cells.
- Meiosis: 4 haploid cells; crossing over in prophase I; germ cells.
- Mitosis stages trick: “I Prefer Meat At Taco Bell” (Interphase, Prophase, Metaphase, Anaphase, Telophase). 【turn1fetch0】

