## 4) Human Physiology (High Weightage)

### Digestion and absorption
- Mouth: salivary amylase (ptyalin) digestion of starch; lysozyme antibacterial.
- Stomach: pepsin (protease); gastric lipase; HCl → kills bacteria, activates pepsinogen; mucus protects.
- Small intestine: pancreatic enzymes (trypsin, chymotrypsin, amylase, lipase); bile salts emulsify fats; brush border enzymes (maltase, lactase, peptidases); site of absorption.
- Large intestine: water absorption; gut microbiome (vitamin K, B12 synthesis).

### Respiration in humans
- Breathing rate: 12–16/min; tidal volume ~500 mL.
- Vital capacity: IRV + TV + ERV.
- Transport of O2/CO2: O2 mainly as oxyhaemoglobin (HbO2); CO2 as carbaminohaemoglobin, bicarbonate, dissolved.
- Bohr effect: O2 release favoured in high pCO2, low pH, high temperature.

### Circulatory system
- Heart chambers: 2 atria, 2 ventricles; left ventricle thickest wall.
- Conduction system: SA node → AV node → AV bundle → Purkinje fibres (SA node is pacemaker).
- Heart valves order: “Try Pulling My Aorta” (Tricuspid, Pulmonary, Mitral, Aortic). 【turn1fetch0】
- Double circulation: pulmonary (heart → lungs → heart) + systemic (heart → body → heart).

### Blood components
- RBCs: biconcave; anucleate; haemoglobin; EPO (kidney) stimulates RBC formation.
- WBCs: neutrophils (phagocytosis), lymphocytes (immune), eosinophils (allergy, parasites), basophils (heparin, histamine), monocytes (macrophages).
- Platelets: cell fragments; clotting.

### Excretory system
- Nephron functional unit: glomerulus (filtration) + Bowman’s capsule + PCT + loop of Henle + DCT + collecting duct.
- JGA (juxtaglomerular apparatus): juxtaglomerular cells (renin secretion) + macula densa (Na+ sensing).
- Counter-current multiplier in loop of Henle (concentrates urine).
- Hormones: ADH increases water reabsorption; aldosterone increases Na+ reabsorption/K+ excretion; ANF (atrial natriuretic factor) lowers blood pressure.

### Neural control and endocrine system
- Parts: CNS (brain + spinal cord); PNS (somatic + autonomic).
- Autonomic: sympathetic (fight/flight) vs parasympathetic (rest/digest).
- Brain: cerebrum (higher functions), cerebellum (coordination/balance), pons (respiration), medulla (vital centres), hypothalamus (thermoregulation, hunger, thirst, pituitary control).
- Cranial nerves (12): “Oh Oh Oh To Touch And Feel Very Green Vegetables AH!” (Olfactory, Optic, Oculomotor, Trochlear, Trigeminal, Abducens, Facial, Vestibulocochlear, Glossopharyngeal, Vagus, Accessory, Hypoglossal). 【turn1fetch0】

### Endocrine glands and key hormones
- Hypothalamus: releasing/inhibiting hormones; oxytocin & ADH made here, stored in posterior pituitary.
- Pituitary: anterior (GH, prolactin, TSH, ACTH, FSH, LH); posterior (oxytocin, ADH).
- Thyroid: T3/T4 regulate BMR; calcitonin lowers blood Ca2+.
- Parathyroid: PTH increases blood Ca2+.
- Adrenal medulla: adrenaline/epinephrine; cortex: cortisol, aldosterone.
- Pancreas: islets of Langerhans – α cells (glucagon), β cells (insulin).
- Gonads: testes (testosterone); ovary (estrogen, progesterone).
- Pineal: melatonin (sleep–wake cycle); thymus: T cells maturation.

