## 5) Reproduction in Organisms (Plants & Humans)

### Asexual reproduction
- Binary fission, budding, fragmentation, spores, vegetative propagation.
- Vegetative propagation: runners, suckers, tubers, offsets, bulbils.

### Sexual reproduction in flowering plants
- Stamen: anther (pollen sacs) + filament.
- Carpel: stigma + style + ovary (ovules).
- Microsporogenesis: diploid microspore mother cells → haploid microspores → pollen grain.
- Megasporogenesis: megaspore mother cell → 4 megaspores → 1 functional (8-nucleate embryo sac).
- Pollination: biotic (insects, birds) and abiotic (wind, water).
- Double fertilization: one sperm fuses with egg (zygote); another with two polar nuclei (endosperm, PEC).
- Post-fertilization: seed (embryo + endosperm/seed coat) + fruit.

### Human reproduction
- Male: testes (spermatogenesis in seminiferous tubules); Leydig cells (androgens); Sertoli cells (nourishment); epididymis, vas deferens, seminal vesicle, prostate, bulbourethral gland.
- Female: ovary (oogenesis, ovulation); fallopian tube (site of fertilization); uterus (implantation); cervix, vagina.
- Menstrual cycle: follicular phase (proliferative endometrium), ovulation (~day 14), luteal phase (secretory endometrium); if no implantation → menstruation.
- Hormones: FSH, LH (pituitary); estrogen, progesterone (ovary); hCG (pregnancy test).

