## 8) Human Health and Diseases

### Immunity types
- Innate (non-specific): physical barriers, phagocytes, complement.
- Acquired (specific): active (infection/vaccine) vs passive (antibodies transferred).

### Types of immunity
- Active natural: infection.
- Active artificial: vaccination.
- Passive natural: maternal antibodies (placenta/colostrum).
- Passive artificial: antibody injection (antisera).

### Diseases (quick tags)
- Bacterial: typhoid (Salmonella), pneumonia (Streptococcus), cholera (Vibrio).
- Viral: HIV (AIDS), rabies, mumps, measles, dengue, chikungunya, COVID-19.
- Protozoan: malaria (Plasmodium), amoebiasis (Entamoeba), sleeping sickness (Trypanosoma).
- Fungal: ringworm, athlete’s foot.

### Life cycle of Plasmodium (malaria)
- Female Anopheles mosquito bites → sporozoites → liver (schizogony) → merozoites → RBCs → gametocytes → mosquito (gametogenesis → fertilization → oocyst → sporozoites).

