## 11) Common Vitamins, Deficiencies & Mnemonic

Vitamins and deficiencies are often repeated.

- Vitamin A: night blindness, xerophthalmia.
- B1 (thiamine): beri-beri.
- B2 (riboflavin): cheilosis, angular stomatitis.
- B3 (niacin): pellagra (3 D’s: diarrhoea, dermatitis, dementia).
- B6 (pyridoxine): anaemia, neurological symptoms.
- B9 (folic acid): megaloblastic anaemia; neural tube defects.
- B12 (cobalamin): pernicious anaemia; neurological issues.
- C (ascorbic acid): scurvy (bleeding gums).
- D: rickets (children), osteomalacia (adults).
- E: infertility, neurological problems.
- K: bleeding disorders (clotting).

Trick for fat-soluble vitamins: “ADEK” (All Dead Elephants Kicked? Just remember A, D, E, K are fat-soluble; water-soluble: B-complex + C).

